Creating a post-modern style for your wiki website involves embracing bold colors, asymmetrical layouts, experimental typography, and unconventional design elements. Here's some CSS to give your wiki that post-modern flair:

```css
body {
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
    background-color: #000;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    background-color: #ff2d55;
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
}

h1 {
    font-size: 3em;
    margin: 0;
}

main {
    padding: 20px;
}

section#content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
}

article {
    background-color: #333;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

h2 {
    font-size: 1.5em;
    margin-top: 0;
}

p {
    font-size: 1em;
    line-height: 1.5;
}

button {
    background-color: #ff2d55;
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    font-size: 1em;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #ff5e7d;
}

footer {
    background-color: #ff2d55;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
}

footer p {
    margin: 0;
}
```

This CSS provides a bold and vibrant look for your wiki website. Adjust the colors, fonts, and layout as needed to achieve the desired post-modern aesthetic.